032@SuppressWarnings({
033    "PMD.DataClass",
034    "PMD.FieldNamingConventions"
035})
036@MetaschemaAssembly(
037    formalName = "Allowed Values Constraint",
038    name = "flag-allowed-values",
039    moduleClass = MetaschemaModelModule.class)
040public class FlagAllowedValues implements IBoundObject, IConstraintBase {
041  private final IMetaschemaData __metaschemaData;
042
043  @BoundFlag(
044      formalName = "Constraint Identifier",
045      name = "id",
046      typeAdapter = TokenAdapter.class)
047  private String _id;
048
049  @BoundFlag(
050      formalName = "Constraint Severity Level",
051      name = "level",
052      defaultValue = "ERROR",
053      typeAdapter = TokenAdapter.class,
054      valueConstraints = @ValueConstraints(allowedValues = @AllowedValues(level = IConstraint.Level.ERROR, values = {
055          @AllowedValue(value = "CRITICAL",
056              description = "A violation of the constraint represents a serious fault in the content that will prevent typical use of the content."),
057          @AllowedValue(value = "ERROR",
058              description = "A violation of the constraint represents a fault in the content. This may include issues around compatibility, integrity, consistency, etc."),
059          @AllowedValue(value = "WARNING",
060              description = "A violation of the constraint represents a potential issue with the content."),
061          @AllowedValue(value = "INFORMATIONAL",
062              description = "A violation of the constraint represents a point of interest."),
063          @AllowedValue(value = "DEBUG",
064              description = "A violation of the constraint represents a fault in the content that may warrant review by a developer when performing model or tool development.") })))
065  private String _level;
066
067  @BoundFlag(
068      formalName = "Allow Non-Enumerated Values?",
069      name = "allow-other",
070      defaultValue = "no",
071      typeAdapter = TokenAdapter.class,
072      valueConstraints = @ValueConstraints(allowedValues = @AllowedValues(level = IConstraint.Level.ERROR,
073          values = { @AllowedValue(value = "no", description = "Other values are not allowed."),
074              @AllowedValue(value = "yes", description = "Other values are allowed.") })))
075  private String _allowOther;
076
077  /**
078   * "Determines if the given enumerated values may be extended by other allowed
079   * value constraints."
080   */
081  @BoundFlag(
082      formalName = "Allow Extension?",
083      description = "Determines if the given enumerated values may be extended by other allowed value constraints.",
084      name = "extensible",
085      defaultValue = "external",
086      typeAdapter = TokenAdapter.class,
087      valueConstraints = @ValueConstraints(allowedValues = @AllowedValues(level = IConstraint.Level.ERROR,
088          values = {
089              @AllowedValue(value = "model", description = "Can be extended by constraints within the same module."),
090              @AllowedValue(value = "external", description = "Can be extended by external constraints."),
091              @AllowedValue(value = "none", description = "Cannot be extended.") })))
092  private String _extensible;
093
094  @BoundField(
095      formalName = "Formal Name",
096      description = "A formal name for the data construct, to be presented in documentation.",
097      useName = "formal-name")
098  private String _formalName;
099
100  @BoundField(
101      formalName = "Description",
102      description = "A short description of the data construct's purpose, describing the constructs semantics.",
103      useName = "description",
104      typeAdapter = MarkupLineAdapter.class)
105  private MarkupLine _description;
106
107  @BoundAssembly(
108      formalName = "Property",
109      useName = "prop",
110      maxOccurs = -1,
111      groupAs = @GroupAs(name = "props", inJson = JsonGroupAsBehavior.LIST))
112  private List<Property> _props;
113
114  @BoundField(
115      formalName = "Allowed Value Enumeration",
116      useName = "enum",
117      minOccurs = 1,
118      maxOccurs = -1,
119      groupAs = @GroupAs(name = "enums", inJson = JsonGroupAsBehavior.LIST))
120  private List<ConstraintValueEnum> _enums;
121
122  @BoundField(
123      formalName = "Remarks",
124      description = "Any explanatory or helpful information to be provided about the remarks parent.",
125      useName = "remarks")
126  private Remarks _remarks;
127
128  public FlagAllowedValues() {
129    this(null);
130  }
131

133    this.__metaschemaData = data;
134  }

139  }

144  }
145

147    _id = value;
148  }
149
150  @Override
151  public String getLevel() {
152    return _level;
153  }
154
155  public void setLevel(String value) {
156    _level = value;
157  }
158
159  public String getAllowOther() {
160    return _allowOther;
161  }
162
163  public void setAllowOther(String value) {
164    _allowOther = value;
165  }
166
167  public String getExtensible() {
168    return _extensible;
169  }
170
171  public void setExtensible(String value) {
172    _extensible = value;
173  }
174
175  @Override
176  public String getFormalName() {
177    return _formalName;
178  }
179
180  public void setFormalName(String value) {
181    _formalName = value;
182  }
183
184  @Override
185  public MarkupLine getDescription() {
186    return _description;
187  }
188
189  public void setDescription(MarkupLine value) {
190    _description = value;
191  }
192
193  @Override
194  public List<Property> getProps() {
195    return _props;
196  }
197
198  public void setProps(List<Property> value) {
199    _props = value;
200  }
201
202  /**
203   * Add a new {@link Property} item to the underlying collection.
204   *
205   * @param item
206   *          the item to add
207   * @return {@code true}
208   */
209  public boolean addProp(Property item) {
210    Property value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
211    if (_props == null) {
212      _props = new LinkedList<>();
213    }
214    return _props.add(value);
215  }
216
217  /**
218   * Remove the first matching {@link Property} item from the underlying
219   * collection.
220   *
221   * @param item
222   *          the item to remove
223   * @return {@code true} if the item was removed or {@code false} otherwise
224   */
225  public boolean removeProp(Property item) {
226    Property value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
227    return _props != null && _props.remove(value);
228  }
229
230  public List<ConstraintValueEnum> getEnums() {
231    return _enums;
232  }
233
234  public void setEnums(List<ConstraintValueEnum> value) {
235    _enums = value;
236  }
237
238  /**
239   * Add a new {@link ConstraintValueEnum} item to the underlying collection.
240   *
241   * @param item
242   *          the item to add
243   * @return {@code true}
244   */
245  public boolean addEnum(ConstraintValueEnum item) {
246    ConstraintValueEnum value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
247    if (_enums == null) {
248      _enums = new LinkedList<>();
249    }
250    return _enums.add(value);
251  }
252
253  /**
254   * Remove the first matching {@link ConstraintValueEnum} item from the
255   * underlying collection.
256   *
257   * @param item
258   *          the item to remove
259   * @return {@code true} if the item was removed or {@code false} otherwise
260   */
261  public boolean removeEnum(ConstraintValueEnum item) {
262    ConstraintValueEnum value = ObjectUtils.requireNonNull(item, "item cannot be null");
263    return _enums != null && _enums.remove(value);
264  }
265
266  @Override
267  public Remarks getRemarks() {
268    return _remarks;
269  }
270
271  public void setRemarks(Remarks value) {
272    _remarks = value;
273  }
274
275  @Override
276  public String toString() {
277    return new ReflectionToStringBuilder(this, ToStringStyle.MULTI_LINE_STYLE).toString();
278  }
